One really useful pattern is React higher-order components,
eg. <a href="https://github.com/elierotenberg/react-nexus#componentgetnexusbindings" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/elierotenberg/react-nexus#componentgetnex...</a><p>The pattern is<p><pre><code>  function decorate(params) {
    return (Component) => class extends React.Component {
      ... // some code using params
      render() {
        return <Component {...this.props} />
      }
    };
  }
</code></pre>
my2c.
